Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil 
with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the pasta. Halve the @yellow pepper{1} and 
discard the cores and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Halve and peel the 
@onion{1}(peeled) then chop into 2cm chunks. Trim the @courgette{1} and halve 
lengthways. Chop widthways into 2cm chunks. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{163%g} 
in a #sieve{}.

Pop the pepper, onion and courgette on a large lined #baking tray{} and sprinkle 
over the @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then 
drizzle with @oil{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf of 
your oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, add the @fusilli{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for 
~{9%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. 
Drizzle with @oil{} to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta and veggies cook, cut the @medium tomatoes{2}(sliced) into about 
1cm thick slices. Drain the @mozzarella{1}.

When the veggies are done, transfer them to an ovenproof #dish{} along with the 
wheat pasta and sweetcorn. Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and 
garlic{1/2%can}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir everything together. 
Arrange the tomato slices on top then tear over the mozzarella. Sprinkle over 
the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and bake on the top shelf of your 
oven until golden and bubbly, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once golden share the veggie wheat pasta bake between your plates. Enjoy!